The form one selection launch has been moved to next Tuesday. In a circular to regional education coordinators and county education directors, Education PS Belio Kipsang said the date has been moved to December 13 from December 9. &ldquo;The launch to be presided over by the Cabinet Secretary will take place at 8am at the Kenya Institute of Curriculum Development ,&rdquo; Belio said.The form one admission will still start on January 9. In the past form one students joined secondary school in February. This year&rsquo;s KCPE results were released on December 1, as opposed to the end of December tradition. Education CS Fred Matiang&rsquo;i said the selection will be based on merit, quotas, equity, affirmative action and candidate choices.The selection will also ensure that children from disadvantaged backgrounds continue with their education.&ldquo;I also wish to assure the public that all candidates who scored 400 marks and above will be admitted to national schools, irrespective of their gender, region or centre,&rdquo; Matiang&rsquo;i said.He said admission letters to form one students will be issued before Christmas.